  "steps": [
    {
      "id": "tutorial-vscode-browser-01",
      "markerIndex": 0,
      "replayStartSec": 2.414862,
      "replayEndSec": 12.531234,
      "narrationText": "One command. The CLI installs the editor server on the machine once, starts it inside the repo sandbox, opens a tunnel, and hands you a link. No local VS Code, no extensions to set up.",
      "audioSrc": "/assets/tutorials/audio/es/tutorial-vscode-browser/tutorial-vscode-browser-01.30a85238.mp3",
      "textHash": "30a8523807c0a167969d98c95512dbc39af738b7d0126ea8eb9593631b6215ff",
      "audioDurationSec": 13.635918,
      "afterAudioSrc": "/assets/tutorials/audio/es/tutorial-vscode-browser/tutorial-vscode-browser-01-after.ba3a6df2.mp3",
      "afterAudioDurationSec": 7.706122,
      "afterTextHash": "ba3a6df28286c3bab5154ec92222d511b2de97f8d48461a24294a6b0c1d836c6"
    },
    {
      "id": "tutorial-vscode-browser-02",
      "markerIndex": 1,
      "replayStartSec": 12.531234,
      "replayEndSec": 19.464899,
      "narrationText": "Same repo from the plain terminal: the working directory is the repo, the files are the repo's files.",
      "audioSrc": "/assets/tutorials/audio/es/tutorial-vscode-browser/tutorial-vscode-browser-02.e9155f31.mp3",
      "textHash": "e9155f3135fe90777abdd5a65911d6a40c88cc75aa6c52095a4ccb4ceabf2be8",
      "audioDurationSec": 6.60898,
      "afterAudioSrc": "/assets/tutorials/audio/es/tutorial-vscode-browser/tutorial-vscode-browser-02-after.0f39b084.mp3",
      "afterAudioDurationSec": 4.440816,
      "afterTextHash": "0f39b0843ed438f865af66e18e0aad00255490e5b8c4903d4dc8aeee1fb45239"
    },
    {
      "id": "tutorial-vscode-browser-03",
      "markerIndex": 2,
      "replayStartSec": 19.464899,
      "replayEndSec": 26.768996,
      "narrationText": "And the file we created in the browser editor? Right here. Files made in VS Code are real repo files, instantly.",
      "audioSrc": "/assets/tutorials/audio/es/tutorial-vscode-browser/tutorial-vscode-browser-03.f77b3485.mp3",
      "textHash": "f77b348591307181ff5f7483ae8cf4d107d96bdddabdec602bcef6bf4dbe33b1",
      "audioDurationSec": 8.045714,
      "afterAudioSrc": "/assets/tutorials/audio/es/tutorial-vscode-browser/tutorial-vscode-browser-03-after.96ab1401.mp3",
      "afterAudioDurationSec": 5.799184,
      "afterTextHash": "96ab140197b12ba017c1b5f85736f1fbbca0ef83528b4667bdf09180fd46a789"
    },
    {
      "id": "tutorial-vscode-browser-04",
      "markerIndex": 3,
      "replayStartSec": 26.768996,
      "replayEndSec": 32.439211,
      "narrationText": "Now try to leave. Listing the root of the server: permission denied. The kernel scopes the editor, its terminal, and every child process to this repo.",
      "audioSrc": "/assets/tutorials/audio/es/tutorial-vscode-browser/tutorial-vscode-browser-04.30bd53cd.mp3",
      "textHash": "30bd53cdd9480fa2310c4a1157b0ca770f1c128fe9d91b615853a7e975dfda9c",
      "audioDurationSec": 10.527347,
      "afterAudioSrc": "/assets/tutorials/audio/es/tutorial-vscode-browser/tutorial-vscode-browser-04-after.a5e25b93.mp3",
      "afterAudioDurationSec": 3.317551,
      "afterTextHash": "a5e25b93f68e819c6f8c1c67b190fdecae22c8d34307aab893a2c9075ca78ba3"
    },
    {
      "id": "tutorial-vscode-browser-05",
      "markerIndex": 4,
      "replayStartSec": 32.439211,
      "replayEndSec": 38.211313,
      "narrationText": "Other users' homes? Also denied. Whatever runs inside this sandbox — editors, terminals, build tools — ends at the repo's walls.",
      "audioSrc": "/assets/tutorials/audio/es/tutorial-vscode-browser/tutorial-vscode-browser-05.998877d9.mp3",
      "textHash": "998877d91c830457f33a36e9585263b22b806eff6fac4087e2543fb3e93d1ddb",
      "audioDurationSec": 10.03102,
      "afterAudioSrc": "/assets/tutorials/audio/es/tutorial-vscode-browser/tutorial-vscode-browser-05-after.83d80827.mp3",
      "afterAudioDurationSec": 4.205714,
      "afterTextHash": "83d80827269d464e02894e830f34b9e05b793f1b356a96e2e33475ab14a2f823"
    }
  ],
  "narrationAudio": [
    {
      "id": "intro",
      "textHash": "1b881c74da2ed2e725ea21bfcd815eac21ac11723c5fcd35fdd04c8c9da59413",
      "audioSrc": "/assets/tutorials/audio/es/tutorial-vscode-browser/intro.1b881c74.mp3",
      "narrationText": "Buenas noticias: para este no hace falta ningún terminal. Vamos a abrir VS Code completo directo en el navegador, crear algunos archivos, ejecutar un par de comandos y ver cómo el kernel lo mantiene todo dentro del repo.",
      "audioDurationSec": 13.792653
    },
    {
      "id": "sandbox-concept",
      "textHash": "7b44e41e6a768c24883e04a3f0615d785389395412047f912c6eb628a8cf8feb",
      "audioSrc": "/assets/tutorials/audio/es/tutorial-vscode-browser/sandbox-concept.7b44e41e.mp3",
      "narrationText": "Esta es la idea. El editor no corre en tu portátil. Corre dentro del sandbox del repo en el servidor, y tu navegador llega a él a través de un túnel SSH. Así que el árbol de archivos, el terminal integrado y cualquier cosa que lances desde ahí ven exactamente lo que ve el repo, y nada más.",
      "audioDurationSec": 22.987755
    },
    {
      "id": "workbench-tour",
      "textHash": "f8acab0d15a7b16c70318bbfbad4cc22c040726691356944731e4fe5756d4a20",
      "audioSrc": "/assets/tutorials/audio/es/tutorial-vscode-browser/workbench-tour.f8acab0d.mp3",
      "narrationText": "Y ahí está: VS Code, en una pestaña del navegador. El árbol de archivos de la izquierda muestra el repo, y solo el repo.",
      "audioDurationSec": 9.717551
    },
    {
      "id": "create-file",
      "textHash": "8ad08e187afb86156f2938fc72674a2a60f8db16012a6a35d82a2f2e682b3e55",
      "audioSrc": "/assets/tutorials/audio/es/tutorial-vscode-browser/create-file.8ad08e18.mp3",
      "narrationText": "Vamos a crear un archivo real, sin terminal de por medio. Un nuevo editor, un par de líneas, y lo guardamos como notes barra todo punto md. La carpeta aparece a la izquierda cuando llega al repo.",
      "audioDurationSec": 14.106122
    },
    {
      "id": "editor-terminal",
      "textHash": "2da3099bee110da19eb23941e4900a86a9cf95aabf79f075d2d71b321dfd957b",
      "audioSrc": "/assets/tutorials/audio/es/tutorial-vscode-browser/editor-terminal.2da3099b.mp3",
      "narrationText": "El terminal integrado también funciona, y ahí está nuestro archivo. Ahora intentemos mirar fuera del repo: permiso denegado. Eso no es una configuración, es el kernel.",
      "audioDurationSec": 14.915918
    },
    {
      "id": "next-tutorial",
      "textHash": "474e3b9d75c4ab96967494739df676be1016a7b7a891e06eca661a4ba5b96dce",
      "audioSrc": "/assets/tutorials/audio/es/tutorial-vscode-browser/next-tutorial.474e3b9d.mp3",
      "narrationText": "Navegador, editor, terminal: el mismo sandbox, las mismas reglas. Lo siguiente es la función sobre la que se construye todo esto, el forking. Este te va a gustar.",
      "audioDurationSec": 13.322449
    }
  ]
}
